WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:03.168
- I'm not trying
to get Chili in trouble,

00:03.170 --> 00:05.237
but that woman almost
died today.

00:05.239 --> 00:06.305
- I'll take it from here.

00:06.307 --> 00:07.639
- Think he'd cut her
a little slack,

00:07.641 --> 00:09.008
after all she's been through.

00:09.010 --> 00:10.442
- What's that mean?
- Chili's sister.

00:10.444 --> 00:13.045
They found her body
in a flophouse.

00:13.047 --> 00:14.413
<i>- But what happened</i>
<i>to Herrmann, bro?</i>

00:14.415 --> 00:16.148
- I'm the one
who messed up.

00:16.150 --> 00:18.150
- Freddie couldn't escape
his own nature.

00:18.152 --> 00:20.552
<i>But I'm not ready</i>
<i>to forgive that kid.</i>

00:20.554 --> 00:22.488
- Alex Ward,
Department of Homeland Security.

00:22.490 --> 00:25.524
Just asking for some assistance
on an ongoing investigation.

00:33.199 --> 00:34.700
- It's a beautiful city.

00:36.603 --> 00:38.370
- Yeah, it is.

00:38.372 --> 00:41.373
<i>[somber music]</i>

00:41.375 --> 00:49.415
<i>♪</i>

00:52.085 --> 00:54.420
- Something's on your mind.

00:57.223 --> 00:58.757
- What we busted in on today...

00:58.759 --> 01:01.260
- Don't worry.

01:01.262 --> 01:02.428
We got it covered.

01:06.466 --> 01:09.535
[phone ringing]

01:12.105 --> 01:13.572
Hey, Marty,
can you hang on a sec?

01:13.574 --> 01:14.840
[phone beeps]

01:16.810 --> 01:19.678
I have to ask you
a favor.

01:19.680 --> 01:21.180
- Shoot.

01:23.716 --> 01:25.417
- You weren't here.

01:26.753 --> 01:28.754
- Yeah, no sweat.

01:28.756 --> 01:30.489
- Thank you.

01:32.225 --> 01:33.258
[phone beeps]

01:33.260 --> 01:34.860
Hey.

01:34.862 --> 01:37.196
Yeah, it's already been
sent over to Ernie.

01:37.198 --> 01:38.831
Details will all be
in my report.

01:38.833 --> 01:40.699
Samples have been sent
to the lab.

01:41.801 --> 01:43.302
<i>- I look down,</i>

01:43.304 --> 01:45.704
<i>and all I see is blood.</i>

01:45.706 --> 01:49.274
That's when
the pain hits...

01:49.276 --> 01:51.777
starts burning like hell.

01:51.779 --> 01:54.279
<i>♪</i>

01:54.281 --> 01:56.148
It's like a blowtorch
cutting through my ribs;

01:56.150 --> 01:57.583
that's what it felt like.

01:57.585 --> 01:59.785
<i>♪</i>

01:59.787 --> 02:02.187
And then I see a knife handle
sticking out of me,

02:02.189 --> 02:04.189
and I get sick
to my stomach.

02:04.191 --> 02:07.426
<i>♪</i>

02:07.428 --> 02:09.761
Last thing I remember
thinking about was Cindy...

02:09.763 --> 02:13.132
<i>♪</i>

02:13.134 --> 02:15.300
Telling the kids
how their father bled to death

02:15.302 --> 02:17.436
on the floor of that bar.

02:17.438 --> 02:25.377
<i>♪</i>

02:25.379 --> 02:26.545
- Hey.

02:26.547 --> 02:28.180
Come on in.

02:28.182 --> 02:29.648
Grab a seat.

02:34.354 --> 02:36.655
I heard what happened
to your sister.

02:38.424 --> 02:40.526
I am terribly sorry
for your loss.

02:41.761 --> 02:44.429
- Well, I appreciate that,
Chief.

02:44.431 --> 02:46.732
- If you want,
I'll put a call in

02:46.734 --> 02:48.534
to the relief pool,
have someone come in,

02:48.536 --> 02:50.335
fill in for you.

02:50.337 --> 02:53.639
- I prefer to stay busy,
if that's okay.

02:53.641 --> 02:56.275
- Listen.

02:56.277 --> 03:00.712
When I was a lieutenant,

03:00.714 --> 03:04.316
I lost three men
at the Pulaski Avenue fire.

03:06.352 --> 03:09.888
And I thought,
"Best thing for me--

03:09.890 --> 03:11.657
get right back to work."

03:13.293 --> 03:16.695
Two weeks later, I took my men
into a burning building.

03:16.697 --> 03:18.564
Thank God
the chief ordered us out

03:18.566 --> 03:19.932
before the building
collapsed,

03:19.934 --> 03:24.336
or I would have killed
my whole company.

03:26.773 --> 03:30.909
- I understand
what you're saying...

03:30.911 --> 03:33.612
but, Chief,
with all due respect,

03:33.614 --> 03:36.415
that's--that's different.

03:36.417 --> 03:38.383
- No, it's not,
Chili,

03:38.385 --> 03:40.319
because I wasn't ready.

03:41.387 --> 03:45.290
I wasn't ready
to lead.

03:45.292 --> 03:47.993
Sometimes when your head
hits the canvas...

03:47.995 --> 03:50.796
sometimes it's best
just to stay down,

03:50.798 --> 03:51.830
get your head clear.

03:54.400 --> 03:55.701
- I'm fine.

03:58.671 --> 04:00.405
- Okay, then.

04:01.708 --> 04:04.876
You push the wrong meds again,

04:04.878 --> 04:06.712
someone will die.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.847
- So Brett told you that.

04:08.849 --> 04:10.549
- Believe me when I tell you--

04:10.551 --> 04:12.851
how I found out is the least
of your concerns.

04:12.853 --> 04:15.687
That is two strikes, Chili.

04:16.623 --> 04:18.690
If there is a third,
you are done.

04:19.792 --> 04:22.327
I'm not just talking
here at 51.

04:22.329 --> 04:25.397
I mean in the whole
city of Chicago.

04:25.399 --> 04:26.431
Am I clear?

04:27.800 --> 04:29.701
- Yes, sir.

04:29.703 --> 04:31.837
[alarm rings, buzzer blares]

04:31.839 --> 04:35.974
<i>- Truck 81, Squad 3,</i>
<i>Engine 51, Ambulance 61.</i>

04:35.976 --> 04:39.511
<i>Vehicle fire,</i>
<i>2700 block of Roosevelt Avenue.</i>

04:39.513 --> 04:42.514
[sirens wailing]

04:42.516 --> 04:45.517
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:45.519 --> 04:53.558
<i>♪</i>

04:54.694 --> 04:57.996
[shouting, pounding on windows]

04:57.998 --> 04:59.331
- All right, let's go.

04:59.333 --> 05:00.799
Dawson, Mouch--
ladders.

05:00.801 --> 05:03.035
Herrmann, Jimmy,
with me.

05:03.037 --> 05:06.505
[glass shatters]

05:06.507 --> 05:07.973
Guys, get them out
of there.

05:07.975 --> 05:09.608
- Easy, easy.

05:09.610 --> 05:12.311
We're gonna get you out
in a second.

05:13.646 --> 05:15.714
- I can't move!
Help!

05:15.716 --> 05:17.382
Please, help me.
- We'll get you. Hang on.

05:17.384 --> 05:18.617
Grab that ladder!

05:18.619 --> 05:20.786
You're okay.
You're okay.

05:20.788 --> 05:22.421
[booming]

05:22.423 --> 05:23.422
[all screaming]

05:23.424 --> 05:27.459
<i>♪</i>

05:27.461 --> 05:32.664
[siren blaring]

05:32.666 --> 05:33.665
- Casey!

05:33.667 --> 05:36.968
<i>[intense music]</i>

05:36.970 --> 05:38.570
- I'm all right.

05:38.572 --> 05:40.072
<i>♪</i>

05:40.074 --> 05:42.007
- 51, get a line on that fire.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.909
Squad,
help with the evac.

05:43.911 --> 05:45.344
Ambo,
set up triage.

05:45.346 --> 05:46.845
Battalion 25 to main.

05:46.847 --> 05:48.347
We need an EMS plan two;

05:48.349 --> 05:50.382
send all available ambulances
to this location.

05:50.384 --> 05:51.550
- Hey, Tony,
you check the van.

05:51.552 --> 05:53.118
Capp, you help Truck
with the ladders.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.986
Cruz, you're with me.
- Copy that.

05:54.988 --> 05:56.855
- Dawson, throw
that ladder up here!

05:56.857 --> 05:58.924
[woman coughing]

05:58.926 --> 06:00.992
- All right, get back!

06:00.994 --> 06:04.663
[glass shatters]

06:04.665 --> 06:07.065
- Mouch,
ladder coming on!

06:07.067 --> 06:09.401
- Come on, come on!
Please, hurry!

06:09.403 --> 06:11.002
- Don't panic;
we're coming in.

06:11.004 --> 06:12.537
- You got it.
- Wait there.

06:12.539 --> 06:13.805
- Nice and easy.

06:16.409 --> 06:17.609
You got it?
- Uh-huh.

06:17.611 --> 06:19.111
- All right.
All right, here we go.

06:19.113 --> 06:20.412
There we go.

06:20.414 --> 06:21.947
You're good.
Okay.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.483
- Hey, easy.

06:24.485 --> 06:26.885
Borrelli,
give me a hand over here.

06:26.887 --> 06:28.053
Got her?

06:28.055 --> 06:30.422
- Open the door!

06:30.424 --> 06:32.157
- You got her head?
- Easy, easy.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.458
- Got 'em?
- Yeah.

06:33.460 --> 06:34.893
- Come on, get it out.

06:34.895 --> 06:37.429
Severide, move.
Get this door open.

06:37.431 --> 06:40.766
<i>♪</i>

06:40.768 --> 06:42.834
[all shouting]

06:47.006 --> 06:48.673
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!
- Hey, take it easy.

06:48.675 --> 06:49.908
Take it easy.
- Come on.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.710
Get to the ambulance.

06:51.712 --> 06:54.846
[people coughing]

06:59.118 --> 07:00.752
- Grab his legs.
- Yeah, hold on.

07:00.754 --> 07:03.622
- Seat belt buckle's smashed;
I got to cut it off.

07:03.624 --> 07:04.856
- Okay.

07:04.858 --> 07:06.758
- [coughing]

07:06.760 --> 07:11.763
<i>♪</i>

07:11.765 --> 07:13.198
[sirens blaring]

07:13.200 --> 07:15.467
- 154 is coming in.

07:15.469 --> 07:17.769
154, red adult male
coming your way.

07:17.771 --> 07:19.504
-  <i>Copy that, 51.</i>

07:20.673 --> 07:22.874
- Casey,
progress report.

07:23.943 --> 07:26.011
- Might've
got 'em all out, Chief.

07:26.013 --> 07:27.746
We'll do a final search.

07:27.748 --> 07:29.481
- Smoke is getting thick.

07:29.483 --> 07:30.749
Bus could go up
at any second.

07:30.751 --> 07:31.983
<i>Make it fast.</i>
<i>- All right.</i>

07:31.985 --> 07:33.552
Last sweep.
Herrmann, take the rear.

07:33.554 --> 07:34.686
I'll take the front.
- Okay.

07:34.688 --> 07:37.722
[coughing]

07:40.026 --> 07:41.059
- Okay, that's it.

07:41.061 --> 07:43.228
Casey, Herrmann,
I want you out, now.

07:43.230 --> 07:45.130
- Lieutenant, all clear!

07:45.132 --> 07:47.065
- Clear too.
There's--wait.

07:47.067 --> 07:48.767
No, got another one.

07:48.769 --> 07:50.035
Herrmann,
give me a hand.

07:50.037 --> 07:52.003
<i>♪</i>

07:52.005 --> 07:53.004
- Come on.

07:53.006 --> 07:54.739
- Get her up.

07:54.741 --> 07:56.141
<i>♪</i>

07:56.143 --> 07:57.209
- I hear them.

07:57.211 --> 08:00.111
<i>♪</i>

08:00.113 --> 08:02.113
- Got her head.

08:02.115 --> 08:03.882
- Come on.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.784
- I got her.
- Legs together.

08:05.786 --> 08:07.052
Got her?

08:07.054 --> 08:10.055
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:10.057 --> 08:18.029
<i>♪</i>

08:18.031 --> 08:19.531
- Good job.

08:19.533 --> 08:22.534
<i>[somber music]</i>

08:22.536 --> 08:23.602
<i>♪</i>

08:23.604 --> 08:25.937
[sighs]

08:28.274 --> 08:31.142
- How'd the hearing go?

08:31.144 --> 08:34.112
- I did what the state's
attorney asked.

08:34.114 --> 08:35.780
I said what happened.

08:37.250 --> 08:39.217
- Freddie was there?

08:39.219 --> 08:40.218
- Yeah.

08:40.220 --> 08:41.887
- How'd he seem?

08:43.523 --> 08:45.290
- I didn't ask;
he didn't say.

08:47.693 --> 08:51.196
To tell you the truth...

08:51.198 --> 08:53.298
to me, he looked like
any other convict.

09:01.674 --> 09:02.807
- Hey, Otis.

09:02.809 --> 09:04.109
- Hey, Sylvie.

09:04.111 --> 09:05.677
- Oh, what happened
to the moustache?

09:05.679 --> 09:07.245
I loved the moustache.

09:11.284 --> 09:12.551
- Oops.

09:13.886 --> 09:14.953
- I like it.

09:15.988 --> 09:17.689
- Thanks, Connie.

09:17.691 --> 09:20.692
<i>[soft, upbeat music]</i>

09:20.694 --> 09:27.032
<i>♪</i>

09:32.038 --> 09:34.773
- Hey.

09:34.775 --> 09:37.642
- That was a great night.

09:37.644 --> 09:39.277
- Yeah, it was.

09:42.949 --> 09:44.249
Any updates?

09:44.251 --> 09:47.185
- Uh, no,
but there's this.

09:55.127 --> 09:56.761
- Why is my name on it?

09:56.763 --> 09:59.064
- It's an affidavit stating
how we got into the residence

09:59.066 --> 10:00.765
with the explosive remnants.

10:03.369 --> 10:05.036
SAC's on my case.

10:10.042 --> 10:12.143
It basically says
the door was ajar.

10:12.145 --> 10:14.646
It's a security issue.

10:14.648 --> 10:15.814
- It's a long way
of saying it.

10:15.816 --> 10:17.148
- Well,
federal government:

10:17.150 --> 10:19.150
last bastion
of paperwork.

10:22.088 --> 10:23.688
- You mind telling me
a little bit more

10:23.690 --> 10:25.123
about what we found?

10:27.627 --> 10:29.327
- Uh, it's--it's
an ongoing investigation.

10:29.329 --> 10:30.895
There's not much
I can really say.

10:34.867 --> 10:36.701
- Okay, well,
you let me know what's going on,

10:36.703 --> 10:38.136
I'll be happy to sign.

10:41.874 --> 10:43.341
Think it over.

10:47.046 --> 10:48.380
- Okay.

10:58.391 --> 11:01.192
- Monogamy.
You ever consider it?

11:02.995 --> 11:03.728
- Not really.

11:08.267 --> 11:09.768
- All right,
I'm just gonna say it.

11:09.770 --> 11:11.102
Otis without the moustache?

11:11.104 --> 11:13.938
Maybe not the best call.

11:13.940 --> 11:16.374
- So what's the next step
in the big makeover?

11:16.376 --> 11:20.045
- None.
He fired me.

11:20.047 --> 11:21.379
It'll grow back,
though, right?

11:21.381 --> 11:23.748
[phone ringing]

11:23.750 --> 11:24.749
- Hello?

11:27.086 --> 11:28.920
Yeah, I'll be right there.

11:28.922 --> 11:30.321
Herrmann,
you're acting lieutenant

11:30.323 --> 11:31.890
until I get back.

11:31.892 --> 11:34.893
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

11:34.895 --> 11:36.928
<i>♪</i>

11:36.930 --> 11:38.196
- You here for
the blood drive,

11:38.198 --> 11:39.297
or making a donation?

11:39.299 --> 11:40.365
- Neither, actually.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.933
I'm looking for
a mother and son,

11:41.935 --> 11:43.268
Dawn and Lucas Hicks.

11:43.270 --> 11:45.203
The father died from injuries
in the tornado.

11:45.205 --> 11:46.204
- Give me a minute.

11:46.206 --> 11:49.240
[baby crying]

11:50.976 --> 11:52.210
- Lieutenant Casey!

11:52.212 --> 11:54.279
- Hey.
You okay?

11:54.281 --> 11:55.914
- It's Lucas;
he's missing.

11:55.916 --> 11:57.082
You've got to help me,
please.

11:57.084 --> 11:58.083
- Okay.

11:58.085 --> 11:59.417
How long has he been gone?

11:59.419 --> 12:02.153
- When I got up this morning,
his--his sleeping bag was empty.

12:02.155 --> 12:04.956
- You tell the police?

12:04.958 --> 12:06.291
- Hours ago!

12:06.293 --> 12:08.193
They said, "Wait here,"
but I haven't heard back.

12:08.195 --> 12:09.327
So I called you.
- Okay.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.462
What was he wearing?

12:10.464 --> 12:14.799
- All he's got...jeans,
uh, a pair of Pumas,

12:14.801 --> 12:16.968
and a red sweater
from the donation box.

12:16.970 --> 12:18.837
- Stay put
till he gets back.

12:18.839 --> 12:20.205
I'll find him.

12:20.207 --> 12:21.806
- Okay.

12:21.808 --> 12:24.075
<i>♪</i>

12:24.077 --> 12:32.784
- [sighs]

12:34.821 --> 12:38.456
I just wanted to say
I'm really sorry about--

12:38.458 --> 12:40.358
- You're gonna
rat me out to Boden

12:40.360 --> 12:43.161
and then come over here
and try to apologize to me?

12:43.163 --> 12:45.764
- I meant about what happened
to your sister.

12:47.967 --> 12:49.367
- What do you know about it?

12:49.369 --> 12:51.402
- Well, nothing. I just--
- Exactly.

12:52.438 --> 12:54.873
'Cause it's
none of your business.

12:59.411 --> 13:00.912
- Hey.

13:00.914 --> 13:03.181
Are you a "Wizard of Oz" fan,
Dawson?

13:03.183 --> 13:04.949
- Uh, where is this going?

13:04.951 --> 13:07.452
- Oh, I just wanted
to thank you,

13:07.454 --> 13:08.486
pal, you know,

13:08.488 --> 13:10.488
for nudging me
to shave it off.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.190
- So I'm not fired?

13:12.192 --> 13:14.492
- Oh, no, you're still fired.

13:14.494 --> 13:16.961
It just made me think,
like in the movie,

13:16.963 --> 13:18.229
"You are who you are."

13:18.231 --> 13:19.230
- I'm pretty sure it's,

13:19.232 --> 13:21.432
"There's no place
like home."

13:21.434 --> 13:22.834
- Think about it.

13:25.204 --> 13:27.238
- Christopher Herrmann,
collect call

13:27.240 --> 13:29.307
from Pinckneyville State Prison.

13:29.309 --> 13:31.042
- Regarding what?

13:31.044 --> 13:33.444
- Probably something
prison-related.

13:33.446 --> 13:36.447
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

13:36.449 --> 13:44.489
<i>♪</i>

13:58.304 --> 13:59.470
- Hello?

14:01.440 --> 14:03.107
- Did you bring it up?

14:03.109 --> 14:05.944
- Yeah,
not a good subject.

14:05.946 --> 14:09.380
Yeah, I heard it didn't
go too hot with Boden, either.

14:09.382 --> 14:11.149
So I shouldn't say anything?

14:11.151 --> 14:13.284
- Oh, no, she does not
want to talk about it.

14:17.156 --> 14:19.324
I have a bad feeling
about things.

14:20.259 --> 14:22.227
It's like she's...

14:22.229 --> 14:23.862
driving toward a cliff.

14:25.431 --> 14:27.532
- Okay, okay.

14:27.534 --> 14:29.167
We'll figure this out.

14:33.906 --> 14:35.473
- What was that?

14:37.943 --> 14:40.545
- Freddie's father.

14:40.547 --> 14:42.280
- What did he want?

14:44.550 --> 14:46.084
- He wanted to talk.

14:51.090 --> 14:54.359
- That man is a stone-cold
killer, Herrmann.

14:54.361 --> 14:56.227
He once shot a clerk in the neck
during a robbery

14:56.229 --> 14:57.996
for looking at him
the wrong way, all right?

14:57.998 --> 15:00.064
Whatever angle
he's trying to pull,

15:00.066 --> 15:01.499
don't fall for it.

15:01.501 --> 15:04.102
- I won't fall for it.

15:04.104 --> 15:05.570
Believe me.

15:07.306 --> 15:09.340
- I think you should call Kot,

15:09.342 --> 15:11.142
just in case he's trying
to intimidate you

15:11.144 --> 15:13.111
for testifying
against Freddie.

15:33.599 --> 15:35.667
- Lucas?

15:38.704 --> 15:41.105
I'm Lieutenant Casey.

15:41.107 --> 15:43.207
Remember me?

15:43.209 --> 15:44.208
- Yeah.

15:44.210 --> 15:45.643
You pulled my dad out, right?

15:47.112 --> 15:48.947
- Yeah.

15:52.184 --> 15:54.652
Well...

15:54.654 --> 15:56.721
a lot of people
are looking for you.

16:01.727 --> 16:04.162
- I don't want
to see them.

16:04.164 --> 16:06.664
<i>[somber music]</i>

16:06.666 --> 16:08.132
- I didn't, either.

16:08.134 --> 16:11.035
<i>♪</i>

16:11.037 --> 16:14.038
After my dad passed,

16:14.040 --> 16:17.208
I spent a week
in his room,

16:17.210 --> 16:18.643
just sitting there.

16:18.645 --> 16:22.513
<i>♪</i>

16:22.515 --> 16:25.116
You don't deserve
what happened.

16:26.385 --> 16:28.019
It's not fair.

16:29.755 --> 16:31.723
No one can make it hurt
any less.

16:34.426 --> 16:36.394
- I just don't understand.

16:39.164 --> 16:41.766
I mean, he was fine
when we got to the hospital.

16:41.768 --> 16:46.070
<i>♪</i>

16:46.072 --> 16:48.373
- I was hoping
he was gonna make it.

16:49.742 --> 16:52.010
- [sniffling]

16:52.012 --> 16:55.380
I just miss him...

16:55.382 --> 16:57.081
a lot.

16:57.083 --> 16:59.017
- Yeah...

17:02.354 --> 17:04.689
I know.

17:04.691 --> 17:08.626
<i>♪</i>

17:08.628 --> 17:11.529
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:11.531 --> 17:13.264
- Did you call for a medic?

17:13.266 --> 17:15.466
- Yeah, some homeless dude

17:15.468 --> 17:17.101
is laid out
in the alley.

17:17.103 --> 17:18.736
Got some crazy chick
with him.

17:18.738 --> 17:20.138
- Didn't think
to call the cops?

17:20.140 --> 17:22.173
- Hey, lady,
I called 911.

17:22.175 --> 17:23.341
They the one's
called you.

17:23.343 --> 17:25.243
- Okay, show us
where they're at.

17:25.245 --> 17:27.478
<i>♪</i>

17:27.480 --> 17:28.780
- Over here.

17:28.782 --> 17:31.282
- Thanks.

17:31.284 --> 17:32.383
- What happened?

17:32.385 --> 17:34.619
- Uh, Carlos, he, uh--
he fainted.

17:37.189 --> 17:38.656
- Y'all on something?

17:38.658 --> 17:40.391
- Uh-uh, no.

17:42.428 --> 17:43.795
- You're not on spice?

17:43.797 --> 17:45.797
- No, I mean--I mean,
maybe he was.

17:45.799 --> 17:47.498
I can't ever tell, but me--
I'm straight.

17:47.500 --> 17:48.633
I'm straight.

17:50.803 --> 17:52.470
- Yeah, right,
you are.

17:52.472 --> 17:53.504
- Spice?

17:53.506 --> 17:55.073
- Synthetic drug.

17:55.075 --> 17:56.674
They sell it
as potpourri.

17:56.676 --> 17:59.243
- It ain't illegal
to sell.

17:59.245 --> 18:00.812
They do with it
what they do.

18:04.283 --> 18:05.483
- Minor laceration.

18:05.485 --> 18:07.151
- Pulse.
- Irregular.

18:07.153 --> 18:11.389
<i>♪</i>

18:11.391 --> 18:12.790
- Hey, look.
We're not cops.

18:12.792 --> 18:13.858
You want me to check you out?

18:13.860 --> 18:16.160
- No, I'm cool.
I'm cool.

18:16.162 --> 18:17.762
- [groans]

18:17.764 --> 18:18.796
- Hey, can you hear me?

18:20.233 --> 18:23.267
- Take it easy.
You took a nasty fall there.

18:23.269 --> 18:24.535
- You called the cops?

18:24.537 --> 18:26.604
- Look, baby, you fainted;
I thought you were ill.

18:26.606 --> 18:28.139
- Bitch, I told you.

18:28.141 --> 18:29.774
Don't ever call the cops!
- Okay, okay!

18:29.776 --> 18:30.775
Ugh!
- Hey!

18:30.777 --> 18:31.776
- Uh!
- Aah!

18:31.778 --> 18:33.211
- 10-1, 10-1!

18:33.213 --> 18:35.213
We have a violent patient!

18:35.215 --> 18:38.249
[both grunting]

18:38.251 --> 18:47.558
[both grunting]

18:49.495 --> 18:51.562
- You want some?

18:51.564 --> 18:52.830
Ah!

18:52.832 --> 18:54.165
[sirens wailing]

18:54.167 --> 18:55.500
- You okay?
- Yeah.

18:59.404 --> 19:00.805
- You guys call
for police assist?

19:00.807 --> 19:02.607
- Yeah, that guy
attacked my partner.

19:03.742 --> 19:05.576
- Where you going?
Stay down!

19:05.578 --> 19:06.744
- Hell of a response time, eh?

19:06.746 --> 19:08.513
- Yeah, well, we were just
across the street

19:08.515 --> 19:09.881
grabbing a bagel.
- Hey, man.

19:09.883 --> 19:12.150
That girl just hit Carlos
in the head with a metal bat!

19:12.152 --> 19:13.217
I want to press charges.

19:13.219 --> 19:14.552
- She's tripping.
Check her pupils.

19:14.554 --> 19:16.420
- All right, you're coming
with us, all right?

19:16.422 --> 19:17.488
You can tell us all about it.

19:17.490 --> 19:19.157
- Listen, check her bag!
I'm telling you!

19:19.159 --> 19:21.159
Check her bag.
- Stop squirming.

19:24.530 --> 19:27.265
- Look, I'm not
supposed to have that.

19:27.267 --> 19:29.901
I don't know if it's gonna be
my last strike with Boden.

19:29.903 --> 19:32.537
- No way.
You saved my life.

19:37.676 --> 19:38.943
[indistinct chatter]

19:38.945 --> 19:40.244
- Lucas!

19:40.246 --> 19:41.679
- Mom!
- Oh, thank God.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.481
Oh, thank you.

19:43.483 --> 19:44.715
Thank you so much.

19:44.717 --> 19:47.785
- Yeah,
no problem.

19:49.821 --> 19:52.924
- Rumor's going around
they're closing the shelter.

19:52.926 --> 19:55.693
Honestly, I have no idea
what we're going to do.

19:55.695 --> 19:57.929
- I just found out.

19:57.931 --> 19:59.730
Thank goodness
the boy's all right.

19:59.732 --> 20:00.765
- Yeah.

20:00.767 --> 20:01.832
And you are?

20:01.834 --> 20:04.969
- Colin Becks, alderman
for the 52nd Ward.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.604
Great job
finding him.

20:06.606 --> 20:08.573
- Matt Casey,
Firehouse 51.

20:09.808 --> 20:11.943
- Just glad
you're all right, son.

20:11.945 --> 20:13.411
- Thank you,
Matt.

20:13.413 --> 20:14.545
- Yeah, sure.

20:14.547 --> 20:15.980
- Come on.

20:15.982 --> 20:18.316
- So, uh...

20:18.318 --> 20:19.584
you're closing the shelter?

20:19.586 --> 20:22.787
- Yeah, unfortunately,
the tornado

20:22.789 --> 20:25.289
fell below the threshold
of a national disaster,

20:25.291 --> 20:28.326
so federal relief funds
are scarce.

20:28.328 --> 20:29.827
Mostly, it falls
on the local charities,

20:29.829 --> 20:32.964
which are cash-strapped
on the best of days.

20:32.966 --> 20:34.565
- What's being done
about it?

20:34.567 --> 20:36.567
- Well, I'm here
putting together a fundraiser

20:36.569 --> 20:39.470
for the victims
of our ward.

20:39.472 --> 20:41.939
Having a first responder
there, especially an officer,

20:41.941 --> 20:44.942
would do wonders
for raising visibility

20:44.944 --> 20:47.645
and possibly
some additional cash.

20:49.348 --> 20:52.316
- I'm not really one
for politics, generally.

20:52.318 --> 20:53.651
- You're a
"boots on the ground" guy.

20:53.653 --> 20:54.852
I get it.
- Yeah.

20:54.854 --> 20:56.487
I'm just not really sure
how I can help.

20:56.489 --> 20:58.456
- Which is why it would
mean a lot if you were there.

21:00.292 --> 21:01.359
Think about it.

21:02.995 --> 21:05.997
We need all the help
we can get.

21:12.771 --> 21:14.538
- Hey, Chili.

21:14.540 --> 21:15.740
- What's up?

21:15.742 --> 21:17.308
- I know how small
that ambo can feel

21:17.310 --> 21:19.310
when you're sideways
with your partner.

21:20.679 --> 21:21.846
Hey, look.

21:23.682 --> 21:26.317
Don't hold it against Brett,
all right?

21:26.319 --> 21:28.986
Going to Boden
was my idea.

21:28.988 --> 21:30.588
- Yeah, and I bet
you were the one

21:30.590 --> 21:33.691
that blabbed
about Jelly Bean too.

21:33.693 --> 21:35.860
- We're just worried about you,
that's all.

21:35.862 --> 21:38.562
- Yeah, you got a hell of a way
of showing it.

21:38.564 --> 21:41.465
- Hey.
Knock it off.

21:41.467 --> 21:44.669
Look, it sucks
to lose somebody, okay?

21:44.671 --> 21:46.604
Believe me,
I've been there.

21:46.606 --> 21:50.574
<i>[stirring music]</i>

21:50.576 --> 21:52.677
I'm not trying to tell you
how to grieve, okay,

21:52.679 --> 21:55.346
but you are gonna
lose your job,

21:55.348 --> 21:56.847
and if that's what you want,
fine.

21:56.849 --> 21:58.416
You can keep
pushing everybody away.

21:58.418 --> 22:01.452
But I don't want that
to happen to you.

22:01.454 --> 22:02.553
None of us do.

22:02.555 --> 22:10.594
<i>♪</i>

22:18.503 --> 22:19.537
- Got a minute?

22:19.539 --> 22:21.005
- Sure.

22:21.007 --> 22:24.408
- Somewhere, uh, quiet?

22:28.046 --> 22:30.581
This is completely
off the record.

22:30.583 --> 22:32.550
If you repeat it,
I will deny that I said it.

22:32.552 --> 22:34.452
- Yeah, yeah.
I get the drill.

22:34.454 --> 22:36.454
- Lab analysis came back

22:36.456 --> 22:38.723
from the samples we found
at that apartment.

22:38.725 --> 22:40.458
Along with ammonium nitrate
and diesel,

22:40.460 --> 22:42.526
they also found soap shavings
and camping fuel,

22:42.528 --> 22:43.594
which, as you may know--

22:43.596 --> 22:45.029
- Homemade napalm.

22:45.031 --> 22:46.464
- Exactly.

22:46.466 --> 22:49.800
- So why are you here
talking to me now?

22:49.802 --> 22:52.870
Well, this kind of thing happens
more often than you might think.

22:52.872 --> 22:55.706
Besides, I have ten agents
pulling all departmental pods,

22:55.708 --> 22:57.842
checking all in-service
suspicious person calls,

22:57.844 --> 23:00.511
cross-referencing them with
facial-recognition software,

23:00.513 --> 23:01.946
and at 9:00,
I have a briefing

23:01.948 --> 23:03.614
with the Joint Terrorism
Task Force.

23:03.616 --> 23:07.918
Until then, there's nothing
for me to do but worry,

23:07.920 --> 23:09.754
and I'm not a worrier.

23:11.957 --> 23:14.892
So I just told you
everything I know.

23:18.830 --> 23:20.664
- Okay.

23:20.666 --> 23:21.999
I'll sign your affidavit.

23:24.569 --> 23:27.171
- Oh, darn.
Uh...

23:31.476 --> 23:33.477
I left it
back in my hotel room.

23:35.647 --> 23:37.548
- That's a shame.

23:39.151 --> 23:40.918
- You didn't like it
when I tried to make you

23:40.920 --> 23:42.853
sign the affidavit,
did you?

23:44.089 --> 23:45.623
- No.

23:45.625 --> 23:47.625
- What are you gonna
do about it?

23:47.627 --> 23:50.561
<i>[sensual music]</i>

23:50.563 --> 23:58.436
<i>♪</i>

23:58.438 --> 24:00.871
- Step inside.

24:00.873 --> 24:02.106
Wait here.
- All right.

24:08.780 --> 24:10.781
[buzzer blares]

24:25.063 --> 24:26.797
- Thank you for coming.

24:26.799 --> 24:29.834
[chains jingling]

24:36.541 --> 24:39.143
My boy told me
what he done to you.

24:44.082 --> 24:46.817
You should know
that's on me.

24:46.819 --> 24:48.752
<i>[somber music]</i>

24:48.754 --> 24:51.255
I made him who he is.

24:51.257 --> 24:54.124
I taught him never
to take nothing off nobody.

24:54.126 --> 24:56.560
<i>♪</i>

24:56.562 --> 24:58.896
Believe me,
I'm not very proud of it...

24:58.898 --> 25:01.632
<i>♪</i>

25:01.634 --> 25:04.602
But I used to
take a cord to him,

25:04.604 --> 25:07.671
and if Freddie
didn't hit me back,

25:07.673 --> 25:10.174
I'd hit him even harder
and harder...

25:10.176 --> 25:13.677
<i>♪</i>

25:13.679 --> 25:15.546
Because in my mind,
that's what it took

25:15.548 --> 25:18.082
to survive on the streets.

25:18.084 --> 25:22.219
<i>♪</i>

25:22.221 --> 25:26.624
Listen, I'm not asking
anything for me, all right?

25:27.692 --> 25:30.060
But if you could just consider,

25:30.062 --> 25:33.097
please, for--

25:34.966 --> 25:36.600
Forgiving him.

25:36.602 --> 25:40.037
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

25:40.039 --> 25:42.773
My boy said he ain't
afraid to do the time...

25:42.775 --> 25:45.042
<i>♪</i>

25:45.044 --> 25:46.911
But what he can't live with

25:46.913 --> 25:50.915
is the feeling that
he betrayed somebody...

25:52.984 --> 25:55.986
Who tried to help him.

25:55.988 --> 25:59.023
<i>[somber music]</i>

25:59.025 --> 26:07.097
<i>♪</i>

26:07.099 --> 26:14.905
- Thank you for coming.

26:14.907 --> 26:16.740
You know, they say
that you see

26:16.742 --> 26:18.676
a community's true colors

26:18.678 --> 26:21.045
during times of crisis.

26:21.047 --> 26:23.914
Well, we're all
gathered here today

26:23.916 --> 26:26.083
in support of those folks

26:26.085 --> 26:28.719
who lost their homes
in the recent tornado...

26:31.590 --> 26:34.725
And I'd like to call on
one of our first responders

26:34.727 --> 26:36.694
to come up
and say a few words.

26:36.696 --> 26:39.663
Lieutenant Matthew Casey
of Firehouse 51.

26:39.665 --> 26:42.700
[cheers and applause]

26:46.237 --> 26:47.972
- I don't really have
anything prepared.

26:47.974 --> 26:50.941
I thought it was more
of a symbolic thing.

26:50.943 --> 26:53.811
- Hey, off the cuff
is just fine.

26:53.813 --> 26:55.112
- Okay.

26:56.615 --> 26:58.315
Hi.

26:58.317 --> 26:59.316
[mic squeaks]

26:59.318 --> 27:00.384
[clears throat]

27:02.754 --> 27:05.956
We have a--
a saying as firefighters:

27:05.958 --> 27:07.691
our job's about
running into places

27:07.693 --> 27:11.161
that people are running out of.

27:11.163 --> 27:13.063
Every day we come to work,
we have to be willing

27:13.065 --> 27:18.636
to lay down our lives
for perfect strangers,

27:18.638 --> 27:22.106
so we're taught
not to become overly invested

27:22.108 --> 27:24.274
in the people we pull out,
because...

27:28.179 --> 27:32.149
No matter how hard we try...

27:32.151 --> 27:34.752
not--
not everyone makes it.

27:36.388 --> 27:41.358
These people have already
lost so much:

27:41.360 --> 27:47.131
their homes,
their loved ones.

27:47.133 --> 27:51.935
The one thing they're not gonna
lose is this city's support.

27:51.937 --> 27:54.938
[applause]

27:54.940 --> 27:57.941
<i>[stirring music]</i>

27:57.943 --> 28:06.016
<i>♪</i>

28:11.256 --> 28:13.824
- I owe you both an apology

28:13.826 --> 28:16.193
for jumping down your throats
last shift

28:16.195 --> 28:19.897
and for just...

28:19.899 --> 28:22.399
being a wreck
in general.

28:22.401 --> 28:25.002
- It's okay.

28:25.004 --> 28:27.237
Everybody grieves
in their own way.

28:33.011 --> 28:34.978
- Alyssa was my best friend.

28:37.248 --> 28:40.484
We were inseparable,

28:40.486 --> 28:43.454
especially
after my mom bailed.

28:43.456 --> 28:45.189
In my freshman year
of high school,

28:45.191 --> 28:48.092
she started dating this guy.

28:48.094 --> 28:49.993
I hated him.

28:49.995 --> 28:53.097
She wasn't the same.

28:53.099 --> 28:54.298
She completely changed,

28:54.300 --> 28:55.933
and nothing
that my dad and I did

28:55.935 --> 28:58.502
could get through to her.

28:58.504 --> 29:02.506
And she ran away
and was hooked on drugs,

29:02.508 --> 29:05.042
and then she got busted,

29:05.044 --> 29:07.778
and then that's when
she started working as a CI.

29:07.780 --> 29:09.213
I don't know
if Antonio told you that,

29:09.215 --> 29:11.215
but that's how he knows her.

29:11.217 --> 29:14.284
<i>[somber music]</i>

29:14.286 --> 29:18.021
But he got her out,

29:18.023 --> 29:19.490
and he got her to Kansas City,

29:19.492 --> 29:22.760
and we all thought
that she was gonna be good.

29:22.762 --> 29:26.396
<i>♪</i>

29:26.398 --> 29:27.397
[sighs]

29:27.399 --> 29:29.066
She was missing for three days,

29:29.068 --> 29:32.336
and then her landlord found her
facedown in her apartment.

29:32.338 --> 29:38.342
<i>♪</i>

29:38.344 --> 29:40.410
- I'm so sorry.

29:40.412 --> 29:43.080
<i>♪</i>

29:43.082 --> 29:46.150
- I know that I'm screwing up.

29:46.152 --> 29:47.284
I know that.

29:47.286 --> 29:49.286
I know that I have to get
my act together,

29:49.288 --> 29:51.355
and I know
that I've been on a bender,

29:51.357 --> 29:54.024
and I got to...

29:54.026 --> 29:55.492
sober up

29:55.494 --> 29:58.228
and just start
taking everything seriously.

29:58.230 --> 29:59.997
<i>♪</i>

29:59.999 --> 30:01.932
- Well, we're here for you

30:01.934 --> 30:03.801
every step of the way.

30:03.803 --> 30:12.342
<i>♪</i>

30:12.344 --> 30:15.078
- Ah, congratulations,
Lieutenant.

30:15.080 --> 30:16.079
- Chief.

30:16.081 --> 30:17.414
- I just got off
with Alderman Becks.

30:17.416 --> 30:20.384
Apparently your speech
was a great success.

30:20.386 --> 30:22.920
They've already raised
more than $50,000.

30:22.922 --> 30:24.988
- Wow. That's great to hear.
- Uh-huh.

30:24.990 --> 30:26.990
[alarm blaring]

30:26.992 --> 30:30.060
<i>- Truck 81, Ambulance 61,</i>
<i>Battalion 25.</i>

30:30.062 --> 30:31.595
- Okay.
-  <i>Psychiatric emergency.</i>

30:31.597 --> 30:33.363
<i>6719 Waveland Avenue.</i>

30:33.365 --> 30:36.366
[sirens wailing]

30:36.368 --> 30:39.369
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:39.371 --> 30:47.511
<i>♪</i>

30:47.513 --> 30:49.179
- Chief Boden,
Firehouse 51.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.048
What's the situation?
- Our son, Michael, he--

30:51.050 --> 30:52.616
- He posted a message
on Facebook,

30:52.618 --> 30:54.051
threatening to kill himself.

30:54.053 --> 30:55.352
We think he's been
bullied online.

30:55.354 --> 30:56.620
- How old his he?
- 16.

30:56.622 --> 30:58.222
- Is he on meds?

30:58.224 --> 31:00.257
- He's taking
antidepressants.

31:00.259 --> 31:02.092
- Is there a gun
in the house?

31:02.094 --> 31:03.193
- Not that I'm aware of.

31:03.195 --> 31:04.528
- All right, where is he?
- Herrmann.

31:04.530 --> 31:07.197
- Locked in his room upstairs.

31:07.199 --> 31:08.198
- How many ways in?

31:08.200 --> 31:09.466
- Just the one,
the main hallway.

31:09.468 --> 31:14.504
<i>♪</i>

31:14.506 --> 31:15.505
That's his room.

31:15.507 --> 31:17.241
Right there.

31:17.243 --> 31:18.876
Hey, Michael.

31:18.878 --> 31:20.043
- Please hurry.

31:20.045 --> 31:21.111
- Okay. Okay.
- Hey, bud.

31:21.113 --> 31:23.247
The fire department's
here, okay?

31:23.249 --> 31:24.414
- Hey.

31:26.184 --> 31:28.452
- Hey, Michael.
[knocking]

31:28.454 --> 31:29.920
This is Lieutenant Casey.

31:29.922 --> 31:31.455
You okay in there?

31:31.457 --> 31:33.457
<i>♪</i>

31:33.459 --> 31:35.559
- Come here.

31:35.561 --> 31:37.060
Can you pull the cylinder?

31:37.062 --> 31:38.462
- Not without making noise.

31:38.464 --> 31:40.931
- Giving him time
for who knows what.

31:40.933 --> 31:42.532
- Best option is just
to kick it in and rush him

31:42.534 --> 31:44.067
before he knows
what's happening.

31:44.069 --> 31:46.503
- It's either that
or wait for PD backup.

31:46.505 --> 31:50.107
<i>♪</i>

31:50.109 --> 31:51.508
- Hey, uh, Michael?
[knocking]

31:51.510 --> 31:52.943
<i>[clattering from bedroom]</i>

31:52.945 --> 31:54.244
- Do it.

31:54.246 --> 31:57.114
<i>♪</i>

31:57.116 --> 31:59.383
- Oh, my God!
- No, no, no, no.

31:59.385 --> 32:00.484
- Oh, my God!
- Okay, Okay.

32:00.486 --> 32:05.155
- Got him.

32:05.157 --> 32:06.323
<i>[intense music]</i>

32:06.325 --> 32:07.357
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

32:07.359 --> 32:09.593
Let them do their work.

32:09.595 --> 32:14.197
<i>♪</i>

32:14.199 --> 32:15.933
- Check for a pulse.

32:15.935 --> 32:19.336
<i>♪</i>

32:19.338 --> 32:22.339
[woman sobbing]

32:22.341 --> 32:24.541
<i>♪</i>

32:24.543 --> 32:26.276
- He can't find a pulse.

32:26.278 --> 32:27.411
- Start compressions.

32:27.413 --> 32:30.414
- [sobbing]

32:30.416 --> 32:38.455
<i>♪</i>

32:45.563 --> 32:47.230
- I'm in.
- IV's in.

32:47.232 --> 32:48.465
- Stop compressions.

32:48.467 --> 32:50.667
<i>♪</i>

32:50.669 --> 32:54.004
Charging.

32:54.006 --> 32:55.238
Clear.

32:55.240 --> 32:57.741
<i>♪</i>

32:57.743 --> 32:58.742
- No, no, no, no.

32:58.744 --> 33:00.243
- Again, check for a pulse.

33:00.245 --> 33:01.678
- Yeah.
Come on.

33:01.680 --> 33:05.215
<i>♪</i>

33:05.217 --> 33:06.216
There's no pulse.

33:06.218 --> 33:08.719
- Resume compressions.

33:08.721 --> 33:10.687
- Let me spell you.

33:10.689 --> 33:12.422
Yeah?
- I got it; I got it.

33:12.424 --> 33:15.759
<i>♪</i>

33:15.761 --> 33:16.760
Come on.

33:16.762 --> 33:17.995
- We need to push an epi.

33:17.997 --> 33:21.665
<i>♪</i>

33:21.667 --> 33:23.233
- Epi in.

33:23.235 --> 33:24.301
- Shock him again.

33:25.570 --> 33:26.770
Clear.

33:28.773 --> 33:30.640
- [panting]

33:30.642 --> 33:32.442
- Pulse?

33:32.444 --> 33:39.116
<i>♪</i>

33:39.118 --> 33:40.150
- We got a pulse.

33:40.152 --> 33:42.252
[both exclaim]

33:42.254 --> 33:43.587
- Thank you.
- Jimmy!

33:43.589 --> 33:45.055
- He's going to make it?

33:45.057 --> 33:48.058
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

33:48.060 --> 33:56.066
<i>♪</i>

33:56.068 --> 33:58.802
- [crying]

34:00.171 --> 34:01.238
- Hey, Chief.
- Hey.

34:01.240 --> 34:03.073
Come on in;
have a seat.

34:03.075 --> 34:06.276
So that was a hell of a speech
you gave, Lieutenant.

34:06.278 --> 34:07.811
Someone sent me a link.

34:07.813 --> 34:09.679
- Yeah, thanks.

34:09.681 --> 34:13.316
- So--didn't want you
hearing it from anyone else.

34:13.318 --> 34:15.752
Apparently, they are closing
the shelter next week.

34:15.754 --> 34:16.787
- What?

34:16.789 --> 34:18.388
- Just got a call
from Alderman Becks.

34:18.390 --> 34:21.258
He's, uh, very apologetic.

34:21.260 --> 34:22.626
- What happened to the money?

34:22.628 --> 34:25.529
- Says the operating expenses
were higher than expected.

34:29.734 --> 34:31.802
- Can we give her a treat, Dad?

34:31.804 --> 34:32.803
- Another one?

34:32.805 --> 34:35.272
- Well, she does love them.

34:35.274 --> 34:37.474
- Please?

34:37.476 --> 34:38.475
- All right, listen.

34:38.477 --> 34:40.677
Do not tell Mouch.

34:40.679 --> 34:43.346
She's supposed to be on a diet.

34:43.348 --> 34:46.349
<i>[soft music]</i>

34:46.351 --> 34:53.623
<i>♪</i>

34:53.625 --> 34:55.358
Hey.

34:55.360 --> 34:58.495
Thanks for bringing 'em by.

34:58.497 --> 35:00.864
- Everything okay?

35:00.866 --> 35:02.165
- Yeah.

35:04.469 --> 35:07.270
[dog whines]

35:07.272 --> 35:09.106
<i>♪</i>

35:09.108 --> 35:10.674
Just needed to see 'em.

35:10.676 --> 35:18.682
<i>♪</i>

35:19.884 --> 35:21.585
- So we'll work on that.

35:21.587 --> 35:22.786
- See what we can do.
- Thank you.

35:22.788 --> 35:24.287
- Thanks for coming by.

35:24.289 --> 35:27.224
- Alderman.
- Lieutenant Casey.

35:27.226 --> 35:29.559
I've been meaning
to reach out.

35:29.561 --> 35:31.761
Nice words.
Well said.

35:31.763 --> 35:33.630
- Got a minute?

35:33.632 --> 35:35.398
- Yeah.
Step into my office.

35:35.400 --> 35:36.666
- Great.

35:36.668 --> 35:39.669
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

35:39.671 --> 35:40.804
<i>♪</i>

35:40.806 --> 35:42.539
- What can I do for you?

35:42.541 --> 35:44.207
- I got word
the shelter is closing.

35:44.209 --> 35:46.209
- [sighs]

35:46.211 --> 35:47.677
Yeah.

35:47.679 --> 35:50.147
Unfortunately,
that's true.

35:50.149 --> 35:53.717
- My understanding was we raised
more than $50,000.

35:53.719 --> 35:55.585
- Look, I don't want
to bore you with the details

35:55.587 --> 35:57.420
of how this stuff works.

35:57.422 --> 35:59.289
Sometime, if you want
to spend a day in my shoes,

35:59.291 --> 36:01.591
you're welcome to.

36:01.593 --> 36:04.161
The money doesn't nearly
go as far as you'd think.

36:04.163 --> 36:06.763
There's, uh, hard costs,
operating expenses--

36:06.765 --> 36:07.764
- Hard costs?

36:07.766 --> 36:10.834
Like what, specifically?

36:10.836 --> 36:13.403
- I understand your frustration.

36:13.405 --> 36:15.939
Sincerely, I do.

36:15.941 --> 36:17.741
- Where's the money?

36:17.743 --> 36:19.743
<i>♪</i>

36:19.745 --> 36:21.411
- Okay.

36:21.413 --> 36:23.813
You did me a solid,
speaking at the fundraiser,

36:23.815 --> 36:25.849
and I appreciate that,

36:25.851 --> 36:27.217
but I've explained to you

36:27.219 --> 36:29.219
what the realities are,
Lieutenant.

36:29.221 --> 36:32.255
You don't have to like it,
but that's the way it is.

36:33.558 --> 36:35.358
- Where's the money?

36:35.360 --> 36:37.961
<i>♪</i>

36:37.963 --> 36:39.796
- Nice meeting you,
Lieutenant.

36:39.798 --> 36:44.534
<i>♪</i>

36:44.536 --> 36:45.902
Good luck in your
future endeavors.

36:45.904 --> 36:51.908
<i>♪</i>

36:51.910 --> 36:55.312
- I understand there's something
you want to say, Mr. Herrmann.

36:56.581 --> 36:58.448
- Earlier, I said
I was testifying

36:58.450 --> 36:59.950
because I wanted to make sure

36:59.952 --> 37:02.385
that Freddie didn't
hurt anyone else, but...

37:03.721 --> 37:05.855
That's not the truth.

37:05.857 --> 37:08.258
Not all of it,
anyway.

37:11.629 --> 37:13.964
The day he stabbed me,
he took something from me

37:13.966 --> 37:17.734
I never thought I'd get back:

37:17.736 --> 37:20.470
faith.

37:20.472 --> 37:22.839
And for that,
I wanted him to pay.

37:23.774 --> 37:26.710
But on the job,

37:26.712 --> 37:31.448
you see things
that make you realize

37:31.450 --> 37:34.417
what's important in the world,

37:34.419 --> 37:39.489
and Freddie, he never had
a role model growing up.

37:39.491 --> 37:42.559
His father was
in and out of jail,

37:42.561 --> 37:46.863
and me, I was trying
to fill that gap.

37:49.500 --> 37:51.768
I still am,

37:51.770 --> 37:55.438
because I got to believe

37:55.440 --> 37:59.309
that it's the right thing to do,

37:59.311 --> 38:01.678
no matter what.

38:04.849 --> 38:08.285
So...

38:08.287 --> 38:10.387
if you could find it
in your heart, your Honor...

38:10.389 --> 38:13.390
<i>[heartfelt music]</i>

38:13.392 --> 38:15.725
<i>♪</i>

38:15.727 --> 38:17.961
Please have mercy on him.

38:17.963 --> 38:19.963
- [gasps]

38:19.965 --> 38:22.932
[breathing heavily]

38:22.934 --> 38:30.974
<i>♪</i>

38:31.909 --> 38:33.677
- [clears throat]

38:35.046 --> 38:37.781
There's a deal on the table
for the kid right now.

38:37.783 --> 38:40.817
I want you to know
I don't think he deserves it.

38:40.819 --> 38:41.951
- What is it?

38:41.953 --> 38:44.621
- Drop the charges
down to misdemeanor battery.

38:44.623 --> 38:47.390
He'd be looking at 18 months
intensive adult probation--

38:47.392 --> 38:48.958
basically work camp--

38:48.960 --> 38:51.628
with mandatory counseling
and community service.

38:51.630 --> 38:52.862
After that, free to go.

38:52.864 --> 38:55.498
<i>[somber music]</i>

38:55.500 --> 38:57.067
Judge says it's your call.

38:57.069 --> 39:01.371
<i>♪</i>

39:01.373 --> 39:03.940
- Go for it.

39:03.942 --> 39:06.109
- Okay.

39:06.111 --> 39:07.677
- Yep.

39:07.679 --> 39:15.719
<i>♪</i>

39:21.892 --> 39:23.560
- Agreed, your Honor.

39:24.929 --> 39:27.997
- [crying quietly]

39:29.934 --> 39:32.435
I don't know
why you did this.

39:32.437 --> 39:36.005
<i>♪</i>

39:36.007 --> 39:38.007
I ain't worth nothing.

39:38.009 --> 39:41.111
<i>♪</i>

39:41.113 --> 39:43.680
- You don't know, Freddie?

39:43.682 --> 39:45.648
- No, man.

39:45.650 --> 39:51.788
<i>♪</i>

39:51.790 --> 39:54.391
- Because you and me,

39:54.393 --> 39:57.727
we need this.

39:57.729 --> 39:58.962
Both of us.

39:58.964 --> 40:07.003
<i>♪</i>

40:09.507 --> 40:12.575
- [sniffling]

40:19.550 --> 40:22.619
[crying]

40:22.621 --> 40:30.627
<i>♪</i>

40:35.533 --> 40:37.467
- All right.
You ready?

40:37.469 --> 40:39.002
Loser got to take a shot.

40:39.004 --> 40:40.737
Okay.
Come on!

40:40.739 --> 40:43.773
[laughter]

40:45.709 --> 40:47.043
- Hey, Otis.

40:47.045 --> 40:48.745
- Hey.
Hey, Sylvie.

40:48.747 --> 40:49.979
- Oh, oh, oh--oh!

40:49.981 --> 40:52.916
- Um, hey, how long
has Chili been here?

40:52.918 --> 40:54.751
- Since before I got here.

40:54.753 --> 40:56.119
- Okay, are you ready?
- Go, go, go.

40:56.121 --> 40:58.721
- Okay.
One, two, three.

40:58.723 --> 40:59.856
Two!
- Two!

40:59.858 --> 41:01.524
Ah, damn it!
- Ha!

41:01.526 --> 41:03.159
"Show, don't tell!"
Uh!

41:03.161 --> 41:05.495
[laughing]

41:05.497 --> 41:06.496
- Are you playing?

41:06.498 --> 41:08.465
- I--I'm good.

41:08.467 --> 41:10.600
- Aw, Brett, come on;
it's fun.

41:10.602 --> 41:12.035
- No, I'm good.

41:12.037 --> 41:13.203
- Okay, yeah,
whatever.

41:13.205 --> 41:15.038
All right, Tony.

41:16.540 --> 41:19.142
- Well...
only so much we can do.

41:21.145 --> 41:23.079
- [laughing]
Bottoms up!

41:23.081 --> 41:26.149
[laughter]

41:26.151 --> 41:27.884
- Oh, God.
Okay.
